                            <comment id="14464196" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 20 Jan 2008 05:23:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes I was looking for this option the other day. Did not know it was there actually.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it&apos;s a must that it&apos;s added to the usage description.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14465594" author="levi.yourchuck" created="Tue, 11 Nov 2008 23:39:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, -cp and --classpath on windows do not properly allow spaces in the supplied classpath in 1.5.7.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;C:&amp;#95;sources\src - xxxx yyyy&amp;gt;groovy -cp &quot;C:&amp;#95;deployments\xxxx yyyy\temp_build&quot; groovylink.groovy&lt;br/&gt;
Caught: java.io.FileNotFoundException: C:&amp;#95;sources\src - xxxx yyyy\yyyy\temp_build groovylink.groovy (C:&amp;#95;sources\src - xxxx yyyy\yyyy\temp_build groovylink.groovy)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14478951" author="paulk" created="Sun, 7 Mar 2010 15:26:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should be added to the usage message (probably using header capability)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14479084" author="paulk" created="Sat, 8 May 2010 06:52:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Appropriate help messages added for:&lt;br/&gt;
groovy, groovyc, groovydoc, groovysh and groovyConsole&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
